title: Single Life, It Does Kylie Jenner's Body Good!
text:
Eat your heart out, Travis Scott, because single looks great on Kylie Jenner!

The "KUWTK" star is showcasing her bodacious body in brand new social media snaps, and she's proving a breakup does a body good.

Related:

Kylie Jenner Admits She Wants More Kids Post Travis Scott Split

Travis Scott Reappears On Social Media Following Kylie Jenner Split

Kylie Jenner Living Her Best Life Following Travis Scott Split

Tyga Appears To Troll Ex Kylie Jenner Over $3 Million Bugatti Controversy

Kylie Jenner Has Wild Night Out With Girlfriends Following Travis Scott Breakup

Sizzling with confidence while wearing a skintight black leather mini dress, Kylie stated she "couldn't resist" sharing the snaps with fans on Tuesday.

The barely-there dress with plunging neckline hugged her curves in the best way possible, proving that she's ready to take the world by storm.

Crossing her legs, she's proudly showing off her scar too -- the ultimate sign she's comfortable in her own skin.

The Breakup!

Pairing her lewk with caged flats and a mini purse, Kylie let her long hair flow with her come hither look.

As The Blast reported, the Kylie Cosmetics founder and the "Astroworld" rapper called it quits early this month after two years of dating.

Sources familiar with the situation told us they've "been drifting apart for a while. They tried hard to make it work but ultimately they need to take some time apart."

Adding, they've "broke up and gotten back together several times," so it's unknown if this will be permanent, but fans saw signs there was trouble in paradise.

Kylie Wins!

As for Kylie, she's continued to live her best life post-split.

The youngest billionaire has had business on the brain and has spent ample time with Stormi since the breakup.

We've learned custody of the one-year-old has already been hammered out and the duo will share their time with her 50/50.

Travis Falls!

Travis Scott's career is booming too.

He recently thanked fans for their support after his new song stole the #1 spot on Billboard's Hot 100.

The rapper also performed the Rolling Loud Festival over the weekend, which didn't go so well when he took a big tumble.
description: Single looks good on Kylie Jenner.
